methods.name: public Builder setCredentialEntries(@NonNull List<Entry> credentialEntries)
methods.comment: Sets the list of credential candidates to be displayed to the user.

methods.name: public Builder setActionChips(@NonNull List<Entry> actionChips)
methods.comment: Sets the list of action chips to be displayed to the user.

methods.name: public Builder setAuthenticationEntries(@NonNull List<AuthenticationEntry> authenticationEntry)
methods.comment: Sets the authentication entry to be displayed to the user.

methods.name: public Builder setRemoteEntry(@Nullable Entry remoteEntry)
methods.comment:
* Sets the remote entry to be displayed to the user.
         *
         * The system service should only set this entry to non-null if it has validated that
         * the given provider does have the permission to set this value. Null means there is
         * no valid remote entry for display.
